cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO), as it proposes a novel method for monocular depth estimation that can be applied to robotic platforms. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new deep network architecture, which involves training on unlabeled data, indicating that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper discusses a new dataset for urban driving, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of graphics (GR) as it involves generating ground-truth depth from LiDAR data.
